<p class="head">25<sup>th</sup> August, Continued</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">to find an Opportunity to Converse with them, a<span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> not an Easy thing as they were Strickly watc<span class="AddHand-editors">[hed]</span> <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> Interpreter, however, being prevail'd on by M<sup>r</sup> Goo<span class="AddHand-editors">[dwi]</span>n to remain here all Night, as it now blew a Storme, with So<span class="AddHand-editors">[me]</span> heavy Showers of Rain<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[I]</span>n the Evening I found an App<span class="AddHand-editors">[or]</span>tunity to Speak to One of them, and Invited him to Co<span class="AddHand-editors">[me]</span> next Day to my Tent with his Brother, that I had So<span class="AddHand-editors">[me]</span>thing to say to them, and wished to make them a pr<span class="AddHand-editors">[e]</span>sent, as I very well Knew that an Indian is but little Influenced by Words, unless Accompanied by Something more Substantial<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>e promised me they would Come to m<span class="AddHand-editors">[y]</span> Tent, as the distance was no more than five Miles<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Some people Unacquainted with the Nature of the <span class="AddHand-editors">[In]</span>dian trade, will reckon my behaviour very ru<span class="AddHand-editors">[de]</span> and Say that I make very ungratefull returns for <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span> Polite hospitality I received here, and andeed I must own, that I am not altogether reconciled to the propriety <span class="AddHand-editors">[o]</span>f this behaviour, although it is a very Common Cust<span class="AddHand-editors">[om]</span> in this Country, which nothing but the Nature of <span class="AddHand-editors">[the]</span> Business Can make Excuseable<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>

